revision.text: {{also|Ybañez|Ybáñez}} ==English== ===Etymology=== Anglicization of {{bor|en|es|Ybáñez}}, variant of {{m|es|Ibáñez}}. A surname common in the Philippines and Argentina. {{doublet|en|Ibanez}}. ===Proper noun=== {{en-proper noun|Ybanezes}} # {{surname|en|Hispanic and Filipino|from=Spanish}}. ===Statistics=== * According to the 2010 United States Census, ''Ybanez'' is the 16734<sup>th</sup> most common surname in the United States, belonging to 1709 individuals. ''Ybanez'' is most common among Hispanic/Latino (64.77%) and Asian/Pacific Islander (24.34%) individuals. ===Anagrams=== * {{anagrams|en|a=abenyz|Zeynab}}
